b'#LLBeanPartner Dineo Dowd (@dineodowd) is an outdoor enthusiast and author of four children\'s books about hiking, camping and spending time outside: "I wrote these books to encourage all children of color from different cultures and background to step outside and enjoy nature, because the outside is for everyone. All it takes for a child  to become inspired is to see a photo of someone in nature who looks like them." Keep an eye out for more great photos and thoughts from Dineo in the weeks to come!'
b'Winter, spring, summer, fall - you just have to get outside and roll with it. #BeanOutsider #LLBeanStudents (:camera:: @belladzii)'

b'We teamed up with #LLBeanAmbassador The Bowman Family (@theamericanfieldtrip) to start the #50mileswithin50miles challenge: discover or rediscover local trails by hiking 50 miles within 50 miles of your house. Check out @theamericanfieldtrip to learn how to participate - and maybe even win an L.L.Bean gift card.'
b"From sunrise to sunset, from the mountains to the water, there's no place we'd rather be than outside. #BeanOutsider (:camera:: @userwiththatnamealreadyexists)"

b'Due to the challenges of the pandemic, kids are spending a lot more time online and too little time outside. To provide fun and easy ways for kids to go from screen time to green time, we\xe2\x80\x99ve forged a new partnership with the @nationalwildlife Federation. The program, called \xe2\x80\x9cThe Green Hour,\xe2\x80\x9d includes seasonal activities designed to encourage kids to spend more time outdoors. We will be sharing these activities every week, so stay tuned! #GreenHour'

b'Outdoor adventurer, yoga instructor and #LLBeanPartner Siedah Quirk (@siedah_quirk) shares her outdoor experiences in a way that makes them inviting and inspiring for anybody who loves getting outside. We asked why being outside is important to her: "Being outside is important to me because it truly brings me joy. Nature reminds us of how vast the world is and how we must cherish the planet and those who live on it." Stay tuned for more photos and insights from Siedah in the weeks ahead.'
b'Walking a fine line.  #BeanOutsider (:camera:: @picardfamilyadventures)'

b'#LLBeanPartner Joshua Walker (@joshyoutrippin and host of "Josh You Trippin: A Black Guy\'s Travel Podcast") is helping the outdoors community have important conversations about diversity, access and what it means to belong outside. In his latest blog post, "Exposure Access And Opportunity\xe2\x80\xa6Mental Health And The Outdoors," Josh talks about the mental, physical and social hurdles that can keep us from getting outdoors, and why it\'s always rewarding and restorative to face those challenges and get out there. It\'s a must-read. Swipe up in our IG stories to check it out. #BeanOutsider'

b'Our partner @hikeitbaby has created a fantastic FREE resource for helping your family connect with nature! Download the Thankful for Nature Journal for inspiration to get outside more this November at hikeitbaby.com. #BeanOutsider (:camera: Monique Vargas)'

b'Watch how L.L.Bean, @trustforpublicland and one of Cleveland\xe2\x80\x99s strongest communities worked together to plant trees, custom design a basketball court and make the outdoors more accessible. Watch the full series at llbean.com. #BeanOutsider'

b'Meet #LLBeanPartner Isaiah Scott (@ikesbirdinghikes), a young ornithologist and nature photographer, and the owner of Ike\'s Birding Hikes.  We asked him about the challenges he faced when he first entered the field: \xe2\x80\x9cA big challenge for me was to have my voice heard as a young Black birder. Coming into this field, I knew there was a lack of diversity and very few people that looked like me. I felt alone and unrepresented. But when I continued bird photography and connected with more people through social media, I discovered other Black/POC in this field. Also #blackbirdersweek shed light on many black birders and allowed me to be heard and represented. I want to make sure no one feels the way I did coming into birdwatching and nature photography." We can\'t wait to share more of Isaiah\'s thoughts and photos with you in the weeks to come!'

b'We love sharing the recipients of the L.L.Bean Community Award with you \xe2\x80\x93 each one helps people in under-resourced communities experience the healthy benefits of time outdoors. Healthy benefits are at the heart of the Callicoon Riverside Park project in Callicoon, NY.
 
Public recreational opportunities are few and far between in Callicoon, and by providing access to 47.5 acres of forest and fields and 4,000 feet of riverfront, this park project will create a critical new public access point on the Upper Delaware River \xe2\x80\x93 the only county park with direct access. New trails and other outdoor amenities will offer the community even more ways to enjoy the outdoors.
 
This year\xe2\x80\x99s three award winners bring us closer to the goal of providing access to a quality park within a 10-minute walk of every person in America. Over our 5-year partnership with @trustforpublicland, we will help fund a minimum of 15 projects, which we look forward to sharing with you. Learn more: https://bit.ly/2ByUPDF (:camera_with_flash:: @trustforpublicland)'

b'We created the L.L.Bean Community Award to help fund projects that will enable people in under-resourced communities to experience the healthy benefits of time outdoors. The Huntington Community Forest project in Huntington, VT, won\xe2\x80\x99t just help people get outside \xe2\x80\x93 it will create a whole new outdoor space for them to enjoy.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
Situated next to the Brewster Pierce Memorial School, the new 245-acre Huntington Community Forest will both foster outdoor learning and instill a love of the outdoors in local kids. An uncrowded alternative to nearby Camel\xe2\x80\x99s Hump State Park, the forest will enhance the existing Outdoor Education program at BPMS, and provide opportunities for volunteering and outdoor activities.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
This year\xe2\x80\x99s three award winners bring us closer to the goal of providing access to a quality park within a 10-minute walk of every person in America. Over our 5-year partnership with The Trust for Public Land, we will help fund a minimum of 15 projects, which we look forward to sharing with you. Learn more: https://bit.ly/2ByUPDF (:camera_with_flash:: @trustforpublicland'

b'Each project that receives an L.L.Bean Community Award is different, but they all share the same goal: helping people in under-resourced communities experience the healthy benefits of spending time outdoors. A new project in Newark, NJ, is uniquely suited to helping the community grow. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
The Rider Farm Greenhouse project will transform a one-acre schoolyard at West Side High School with a hydroponic greenhouse, outdoor kitchen, seating areas, new paving, walkways and landscaping. In this revitalized outdoor space, the community will have access to a beautiful new park, and students will have the opportunity to learn about agriculture, business and health \xe2\x80\x93 the city\xe2\x80\x99s first-ever urban agriculture curriculum. \xe2\xa0\x80

b'We\xe2\x80\x99ve taken the past few days and weeks to listen and learn. We believe we have a responsibility to use our voice, our platform, and our resources to help eradicate racial injustice \xe2\x80\x93 because Black Lives Matter. We also believe meaningful, sustainable change will require ongoing commitment. Visit the link in our bio to read more about our efforts.'

b'L.L.Bean\xe2\x80\x99s purpose is to inspire and enable people to experience the restorative power of the outdoors. That purpose, however, can only be fulfilled if the outdoors is inclusive and safe for everyone, not just for some.

We are deeply saddened by the tragedy and unrest our country has experienced in the past few days. Discrimination and racism have no place in our world. Every individual should be welcome and safe at work, at home, in their communities, and in the outdoors.

And while our company was built on the principle of treating all customers and employees with respect and care, we know we must always challenge ourselves to listen, learn and do more. There is a lot of work yet to be done. That begins with taking a hard look at ourselves at L.L.Bean and working with our partners to truly affect change in our communities and in the outdoor industry as a whole. We are committed to being part of that change.

We stand in solidarity with our neighbors, friends and community members. We join you in advocating for change and equality \xe2\x80\x93 for a more inclusive and welcoming world, inside and outside. Our L.L.Bean community commits to listening, engaging and demanding a more equitable world for everyone.'

b'The final stop on our National Park Week \xe2\x80\x9cVirtual Vacation\xe2\x80\x9d is @AcadiaNPS, right here in our home state of Maine. The first national park east of the Mississippi River, Acadia is filled with mountains to hike, beaches to walk and unique carriage roads perfect for exploring by bike. Check out our Instagram Story for a timelapse video that allows you to experience a day in the park, from sunrise over Cadillac Mountain to sunset at Sand Beach. #FindYourPark #EncuentraTuParque https://bit.ly/2yz8kBP'

b'The third stop on our National Park Week \xe2\x80\x9cVirtual Vacation\xe2\x80\x9d is America\xe2\x80\x99s first national park: @YellowstoneNPS. Stretching across parts of Idaho, Montana and Wyoming, Yellowstone is filled with natural wonders that can be experienced through a huge variety of virtual tours. Check out our Instagram Story to start exploring canyons, geysers, hot springs and volcanoes from the comfort of your own home.'

b'The second stop on our National Park Week \xe2\x80\x9cVirtual Vacation\xe2\x80\x9d is @missionsnps \xe2\x80\x93 a piece of a @UNESCO World Heritage Site preserving four Spanish frontier missions in San Antonio, Texas. b'As a family-owned, values-driven company, nothing is more important during these challenging times than the health and well-being of our employees, customers and greater communities. For that reason, we are closing all U.S. retail locations beginning midnight tonight through March 29. This will include our Flagship stores in Freeport, marking only the fifth time in our company\xe2\x80\x99s history that this location will close (and the first time ever for more than 24 hours). All store employees will receive pay and benefits during the closure.

By making this decision now, we can better ensure the safety of our employees and customers, as we all continue to navigate a rapidly evolving situation and follow the CDC\xe2\x80\x99s guidelines around the importance of social distancing.

L.L.Bean was founded 108 years ago on the simple but profound principle that we\xe2\x80\x99re at our best when we\xe2\x80\x99re outside. Today, more than ever, we believe the outdoors is still the best place to find perspective and connection \xe2\x80\x93 and to help us all feel better. A short walk outside or looking out the window to see signs of spring can be an important counterbalance to the pace of news and information we\xe2\x80\x99re receiving.

While our retail locations will be closed for the next two weeks, our business remains open. Our customers can still find what they need on llbean.com or by phone. If you have questions about your order, our products, or just want to hear a friendly voice, call us at 1-800-441-5713. Rest assured, our teams working across operations \xe2\x80\x93 including our home agent service representatives \xe2\x80\x93 are following strict CDC guidelines, including practicing safe working distances and adhering to additional cleaning protocols.

During this period, our social channels will focus on simple ideas and images that inspire and remind us of the restorative power of the outdoors. If you have outdoor moments that you would like to share with us, we\xe2\x80\x99d love to hear from you.

Thank you for being a valued L.L.Bean customer. On behalf of our 5,000 employees world-wide, we send our best wishes for your health and well-being as we push through this unprecedented challenge together.'
